{% offtopic title="How to explicitly enable the module..." %}
There are several ways to explicitly enable or disable a module: using the `d8 system module` command, setting `spec.enabled` to `true` or `false` in `ModuleConfig/{{ moduleKebabName }}` resource (create it, if necessary) or via the Deckhouse web UI.

Example of enabling the module:
- by using the ModuleConfig resource:

  ```yaml
  apiVersion: deckhouse.io/v1alpha1
  kind: ModuleConfig
  metadata:
    name: {{ include.moduleKebabName }}
  spec:
    enabled: true
  ```

- by using the `d8 system module` command (you need a Deckhouse CLI (d8), configured to work with the cluster):

  ```shell
  d8 system module enable {{ include.moduleKebabName }}
  ```

- via the web UI (in the "Modules" subsection, click on the desired module and enable the "Module enabled" switch on the "Configuration" tab, or on the "YAML" tab, set `spec.enabled` to `true` in the ModuleConfig resource):

  <img src="/images/modules-docs/module-enabling-ui-en.png" alt="Module enable/disable interface">

Example of disabling the module:
- by using the ModuleConfig resource:

  ```yaml
  apiVersion: deckhouse.io/v1alpha1
  kind: ModuleConfig
  metadata:
    name: {{ include.moduleKebabName }}
  spec:
    enabled: false
  ```

- by using the `d8 system module` command (you need a Deckhouse CLI (d8), configured to work with the cluster):

  ```shell
  d8 system module disable {{ include.moduleKebabName }}
  ```

- via the web UI (in the "Modules" subsection, click on the desired module and disable the "Module enabled" switch on the "Configuration" tab, or on the "YAML" tab, set `spec.enabled` to `false` in the ModuleConfig resource):

  <img src="/images/modules-docs/module-disabling-ui-en.png" alt="Module enable/disable interface">

